===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|弓|丿|ls=ic|t1=bow|t2=indicatory stroke}}

Oracle-bone and bronze forms depict a (often slack) bow with a short slant stroke added as an indicatory mark; it most likely marks the place/line of drawing the bow (i.e. pulling the string), hence the basic meaning “to pull; to draw (a bow)”. A newer view takes the stroke as pointing to the bow’s curved section (弓淵) and derives “to draw” secondarily, but this remains less certain {{zh-ref|(Sun 2025)}}.

